<chapter xml:id="ch-pythagorean-thms" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The Pythagorean Theorem(s)</title>

  <blockquote>
  <title>Pythagorean Theorem is most important</title>
  <p>
    <q>
      To this day, the theorem of Pythagoras remains the most important single theorem in the whole of mathematics.
    </q>
  </p>
  <attribution>Jacob Bronowski <pubtitle>The Ascent of Man</pubtitle> (p. 160)</attribution>
</blockquote>

<p>
  Given the above quote, it seems only natural to start with The Pythagorean Theorem; 
  a result about right triangles.
</p>

<p>
  What is a triangle? A <term>triangle</term> is a planar figure formed by joining three straight lines, say, of lengths, <m>a, b, c</m>. 
</p>

